Class ArtifactDto

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intland.codebeamer.persistence.dto.base.IdentifiableDto

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseDto, ProjectAwareDto, ReferableDto, VersionedReferableDto, WriteControlledDto, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CalendarDto, CalendarEntryDto, ChatStatsDto, ChoiceOptionDto, InboxDto, ReadOnlyArtifactDto, TrackerDto, TrackerFieldDto, TrackerItemEscalationRuleDto, TrackerViewDto, WikiPageDto, WorkflowTransitionDto

    public class ArtifactDto
extends DescribeableDto
implements ProjectAwareDto, VersionedReferableDto, WriteControlledDto
    An artifact represents an arbitrary codeBeamer object, like a directory, a document (file, wiki page, report). Also artifact comments and attachments are themselves artifacts. Artifacts are revisioned/versioned, so updating the artifact file/content or artifact attributes (except additional info) results in a new revision/version.

      • getDeleted

        public int getDeleted()
        This method is only public because of an implementation side effect. Client applications should never call this method. If an artifact is logically deleted it's deletion level is 1, but if any parent gets deleted afterwards, the deletion level of all descendants is increased by 1, so when undeleting the parent, previously deleted descendants remain deleted. Get the deletion level of this artifact, which is 0 if the artifact is not deleted, otherwise > 0
